Ministers intend to revoke laws banning businesses from using temporary workers to replace staff who are on strike. Business Secretary Kwasi Kwarteng presented the plans, which will enable agency staff to be used, following a ban that's been in place since 1973. It comes as the RMT union confirmed the strikes this week would go ahead, despite last-ditch talks to resolve the issues. Tory MPs have heavily criticised the industrial action, with Dartford MP Gareth Johnson calling them "totally selfish". FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...